tip.text: Lots of choices for zumbarons with interesting flavours. Tequila, cherry cola, malted milkshake, passion fruit and chocolate were good. Bold flavours without being too sweet.

Good crepes, both sweet&savory. Crepes are really thin. If you are looking for something simple,the organic maple syrup crepe is a must order. The ham, cheese&egg savoury crepe is also worth ordering.
Hug mug is a must order. Get the one with dark chocolate to enhance the experience. Very rich and thick.

formattedAddress: Level 6, Westfield Sydney (cnr Pitt St Mall & Market St.)
location.crossStreet: cnr Pitt St Mall & Market St.

tip.text: Can get very crowded especially during dinner. Lots of options to choose from but not particularly a fan of the ramen. Noodles seems to be factory made. The Fukuoka broth however is good.
Truffle mushroom sandwich is my favorite order here. Toasted ciabatta with flavorful mushroom filling. Coffee is roasted in house. Good neighborhood cafe which can be quite packed during peak hours.

formattedAddress: No. 10, Jalan Anggerik Vanilla M 31/M, Kota Kemuning
location.address: No. 10, Jalan Anggerik Vanilla M 31/M, Kota Kemuning

tip.text: Price may be slightly above average but it is justifiable in terms of quality. Personal pick will be the smoked duck and peach pizza. The beer can chicken is sufficient to feed 2 light eaters.

formattedAddress: Level 1 Menara Naza, Platinum Park (Persiaran KLCC)

tip.text: Nasi Kok Kok Ayam Special is good for sharing for 2 light eaters.

formattedAddress: No.8, Jalan Anggerin Vanilla M31/M, 40460 Shah Alam, Selangor.
location.address: No.8, Jalan Anggerin Vanilla M31/M, 40460 Shah Alam, Selangor.

tip.text: The tung poh meat was incredible. Its literally melts in the mouth. So is the homemade golden beancurd in pumpkin sauce. The famed steam chicken is not something I'd reorder (1/4 chicken at RM60).

contact.facebookName: Secret Garden 家園私房菜 Chinese Restaurant PJ

tip.text: The roasted pork belly fared better than the grilled pork ribs. Pork belly was flavorful( with crunchy skin to boot) while the ribs were just BBQ sauce spread over it.

formattedAddress: 10, Jalan PJS 3/48, Sri Manja Square One (Taman Sri Manja)
location.address: 10, Jalan PJS 3/48, Sri Manja Square One

tip.text: Love the service and the food. Very generous with seafood (scallops, prawns, mussels and squid) for the Venetian Pizza. Pizza is thin crust and it is wood fired. Would definitely order this again.
Brunch pasta with 7 mins egg does not feel cloying even when it's cold. The pork chop is very flavorful and meat is tender as well as its 50% fat and 50% meat.

formattedAddress: G13 G Podium Faber Tower 1 (Jalan Desa Bahagia)

tip.text: How can you go to Iceland and not try their famous hotdog stand? The original outlet is the one near the Harbour. I like mine without raw onions and more fried onions.
Rye bread ice cream!So good u'll be tempted not to share.A healthy dessert as its not sweet&does not feel cloying at all.Head to the 2nd floor to get a view of the church while u enjoy your ice cream
Fish soup is really good.Salted cod is too salty for my preference but lamb is a MUST ORDER.Remember to make reservation as this place is very popular. Food is hearty with lots of texture and flavor.

Cinnamon roll is the best! They have 3 variants-cinnamon,vanilla&blueberry licorice.This place is just a stone's throw away from the church,in a colorful building.The scent will lure you into the shop
They serve only 2 types of soup daily - meat or vege. The type of soup is weather dependent. Soup is served in a bread. 1850IKR per soup bowl.
If you prefer something more flavorful, go for Akamaru Tamago instead of Shiromaru Tamago. The Ippudo Pork Bun has too much mayonnaise in it, hence overshadowed the pork.
Kept coming back here for the clay pot chicken rice. This place still uses charcoal stove. One of the best chicken rice in PJ and KL. Rice is fragrant and usually moist.
Coconut ice blended is very refreshing on a hot day and it's not very sweet too.

formattedAddress: The Gardens Mall (LG-203B), Lingkaran Syed Putra
location.address: The Gardens Mall (LG-203B), Lingkaran Syed Putra

tip.text: Portion for the Halibut Fish&Chip is so huge it's meant for sharing.Good enough to last from lunch till dinner for a single diner.Picture does not do it justice.Very generous with the steak fries too.
Pizza alla Diavola is worth ordering. Thin crust pizza top with lots of cheese and pepperoni. Menu says it has dried Chilli but was not spotted on the pizza. Had to request for Chilli flakes

formattedAddress: 50400 Kuala Lumpur, Federal Territory of Kuala Lum

tip.text: Go for the thighs if you want a juicier tandoori. Don't skip the lime. It's essential to add flavor to the chicken. The cheese naan is very fluffy as well. Chicken tandoori RM5, cheese naan RM5.
Revisited this place after 2 years. They managed to maintain the quality of the ribs 👍🏻👍🏻. The platter is quite huge and is reasonably priced at RM299. Could easily feed 6-7 pax.
Smoked cognac and coffee crunchy whiskey are my personal favourite. Buttermilk waffles are light and fluffy. Good to soak up the melted ice cream.
Hainan tea is good. Smooth yet not too sweet. Same goes for the tau foo fah. Love the texture of the fish cake. Has some bounce to it.
Vietnamese dripped coffee with egg yolk. Hard to get this in KL. Condensed milk is provided on the side so you can adjust the sweetness level according to your liking. Coffee is fragrant and rich.

formattedAddress: The Gardens Mall (LG-203B), Lingkaran Syed Putra
location.address: The Gardens Mall (LG-203B), Lingkaran Syed Putra

tip.text: Pork chop is good! Everything on the plate blends to well together. The pesto sauce makes a huge difference to the dish.
Price is friendly, considering it is in the city center. Portion is generous too. The smoked duck with glass noodle is very flavorful, with many slices. 3 cup chicken seems popular.
The salmon sashimi is really value for money.

formattedAddress: Unit 1-6, Level 1, Nexus (No. 7,  Jalan Kerinchi, Bangsar South)

tip.text: Soft shell crab salad is amazing. Lots of texture and flavor in a bowl. Ingredients go so well together.  Very generous with the crab. Good as a meal on its own for light eaters.

formattedAddress: Unit 1-6, Level 1, Nexus (No. 7,  Jalan Kerinchi, Bangsar South)

tip.text: Dark chocolate molten is very thick and rich. Pair it with the berry sauce to balance the flavor. Would prefer if they have more fruits on the plate instead of ice cream.
Salted egg yolk molten cake is truly unique. The combination of curry leaves and corn flakes and crumble goes very well together. Only downsize is the ice cream which does not have much flavor.
Coffee's good (one of the cheapest in town too) and food never disappoint. Good balance of flavor and texture. The creamy chicken and cereal chicken is worth trying. Easy to get parking as well.

formattedAddress: No. 5, Jalan Sri Hartamas 7 (Taman Sri Hartamas)

tip.text: Banana Nutella cake is quite decent. Cake is fluffy with strong banana flavor.
Black Canyon iced coffee is quite good. Strong coffee which doesn't taste diluted even after ice has melted.

formattedAddress: AEON Bukit Tinggi Shopping Centre (Lot F05)

tip.text: If you see the Cempedak cake on display, get it! Light sponge cake with strong cempedak flavour.
Tiramisu is perfect to end the meal. Make sure to add on sambuca. Give the cheesecake a miss. Nothing to shout about.
Cold Vietnamese vermicelli is full with flavour and texture. The lemongrass pork is well seasoned too. Vietnamese coffee could use better coffee powder as it's not robust enough.
It's worth climbing up the stairs. You'll be rewarded with magnificent views. Only wished there's a larger area to swim.
Each room comes with a bathtub jacuzzi. 8 course meals provided on board for lunch and dinner. Happy hour from 5-7pm work cooking demonstration at 6.30pm.
Head to the highest floor (where buffet breakfast is served) to soak in the view of the Old Quarter.
To avoid carbs, skip the bun and substitute it with lettuce. Applicable for chicken teriyaki, fish and shrimp burger.

location.state: กรุงเทพมหานคร
formattedAddress: กรุงเทพมหานคร 10330

tip.text: While the mushroom chicken pie is good, coffee is on the weak side.
If you can only order 2 items, make sure you get the Carbonara pizza and the Portobello. You will leave the place feeling satisfied. They are very generous with the filling for the pizza.

formattedAddress: P-G-020 , Podium PJ Centrestage (No : 1, Jalan 13/1 , Seksyen  13)

tip.text: Be prepared to wait as this place can sit only 25 pax max at one go. The ramen (shoyu base) is worth the wait tho. Go for the large as you will get all the goodness in a bowl.

venue.name: Shimpuku Saikan (新福菜館 本店)

tip.text: The shop only serve one item : katsudon. The dish was perfectly executed. The secret lies in the dipping sauce which made the chicken, egg and rice blended so well together.
Never knew something so simple like scramble eggs can be so awesome. Menu is limited but who cares when the items are all executed well. Coffee deserves a mention too.
Prawn with glass noodle is fantastic. Each strand of noodle is coated in the flavorful broth. Pomelo salad is also a good appetizer. Lots of flavour and texture in a mouthful.

Drinks are affordable for KL standard.Try the Bourbon Bacon Bloody Mary if you are feeling adventurous.Do not leave this place without ordering the Milo Kaw. You will never look at Milo the same again

formattedAddress: 3, Jalan Sin Chew Kee, Off Jalan Pudu
location.address: 3, Jalan Sin Chew Kee, Off Jalan Pudu
location.neighborhood: Bukit Bintang, Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Yummy baked eggs! Not a tomato person but it complemented the dish well & was all polished off. Egg still had some runny texture when served. Homemade ice cream was OK but coffee was on the weak side
The fried pork is good (they call it char siu)! Crispy exterior with well seasoned interior. Go for double portion.

venue.name: Restoran Lou Wong Tauge Ayam KueTiau (老黄芽菜鸡沙河粉)

tip.text: The signature pork burger is so good! Pork is tender and flavorful. Served with pickled vegetables which goes well with the burger
Cocktails with a twist. Think bacon, lemongrass and kaffir leaves in your drink. Worth ordering is the Milo Kaw. Will never look at milo the same way again.

formattedAddress: 3, Jalan Sin Chew Kee, Off Jalan Pudu
location.address: 3, Jalan Sin Chew Kee, Off Jalan Pudu
location.neighborhood: Bukit Bintang, Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur

tip.text: Crispy fried egg is very unique. it retains the runny yolk beneath the crispy edges.
The Big Breakfast lived up to its name. The Catalan baked omelette is good for sharing. Food price here is reasonable for the huge portion.
Nice decor but nicer cocktails! The cocktails itself makes this place worth revisiting.
Lobster bisque is good! Creamy and flavorful. Skip the Bar harbor lobster bake. Go for the snow crab legs instead. The margarita was slightly watered down.
Pad Thai and Thai style pork knuckle - both are really outstanding.
Up The Ante Burger! Pork patty wrapped with bacon, served with raisin bun.
Famous for its Claypot butter crab. The dry curry prawn is worth ordering too. Get the fried mantou to soak up all the gravy.

venue.name: Restaurant Wong Poh 旺来海鲜饭店

tip.text: Go for the Scotch Egg if you want something different. An egg wrapped in their famous pork patty and deep fried to perfection, served on a fluffy bed of mash potato. Satisfaction guaranteed!

venue.name: Restaurant Kui Lam 桂林豬肉粉
